        <h2>BANNER PARADE</h2><small>Posted On: 5/18/2016</small>
        <p>
            <b>THEME:</b> <font style="font-weight: bold; color: red">“Together with Jesus”</font><br />
            <b>OBJECTIVE:</b> To create and parade a resourceful and artistic visual representation of the team’s reflection
            on being one family <font style="font-weight: bold; color: red"><a href="~/events/links/7">“Together with Jesus”</a></font>
        </p>
        <h4>CRITERIA FOR JUDGING:</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Theme Relevance 30%</li>
            <li>Creativity 20%</li>
            <li>Originality 20%</li>
            <li>Recycled/Reused Content 20%</li>
            <li>Parade Costume & Presentation 10%</li>
            <li>TOTAL 100%</li>
        </ul>
        <h4>GUIDELINES:</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Banner size should be at least 3ft H x 3ft W</li>
            <li>Banner should be able to stand on its own (like a display banner)</li>
            <li>No readily-printed materials can be used (such as letter cutouts and computer-printed drawings/letters)</li>
            <li>Everyone is encouraged to recycle and reuse materials</li>
            <li>Artwork should be done by kids and can be assisted by youth</li>
            <li>One Banner Per Area or Per Unit (eg. GA-North Unit, Lakeland Unit)</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h2>Family Got Talent</h2><small>Posted On: 5/18/2016</small>
        <p>
            <b>THEME: Wholesome Entertainment</b><br/>
            <b>OBJECTIVE:</b> To share God’s gift of talent with the rest of the Kids Family Conference participants
            <b>CRITERIA FOR JUDGING</b>: Everybody wins in this talent show because together with Jesus we are sharing our family talents
        </p>
        <h4>GUIDELINES:</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Submit your entry detail (act, participants and duration) on or before June 10, 2016 to kidsforchrist.ga@gmail.com</li>
            <li>Put your entertainment face on to delight the rest of the participants.</li>
            <li>The act must have at least 2 members per family, or per CFC household. It can be a song/dance number, instrument recital, martial arts demo, etc.</li>
            <li>In as much as we want to see more of your performance, please limit your act to five (5) minutes.</li>
            <li>It can be hot and humid during our Kids Family Conference but please no inappropriate clothing/revealing clothes. Only talents shall be revealed. </li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</div>
